				 TV actress accuses cop of assault 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, Oct. 23: A pregnant television actress suffered a miscarriage after a constable and his family allegedly assaulted her for entering their housing complex.																								Roma Dey, 28, was admitted to a private hospital after the alleged beating yesterday but was shifted out today.																								Constable Shankar Sangle assaulted her when she went to his Sarthak Complex, next to her Sunrise Apartments in Goregaon, to drop her two-and-a-half-year-old daughter at her babysitters place, husband Shyam said. 																								Residents of Deys building had barred their neighbours from Sarthak from entering the premises after alleged eve teasing incidents. 																								Sangle, his wife and son assaulted her He kicked and slapped her. She pleaded she was pregnant but they paid no heed, said Shyam, an art director who has worked in Bas Ek Pal and Ek Haseena Thi.																								The couple from Calcutta moved to Mumbai a few years back. Roma has worked in popular serials like Kyunki Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi and Who Rehne Wali Mehlon Ki.																								Roma was shifted out of VN Desai Hospital by her husband, against medical advice. Hospital superintendent Dr Shobha Kukreja confirmed Roma had a miscarriage but could not say if she had been assaulted. The police denied Roma was pregnant. 
